ns to assess her condition, but when Ruby and Iain arrive and recognise her, she runs away. Connie leaves the ward in Ciaran's hands while going to a conference, and he implements a rule where the team have to log their actions on the ward onto an online system, but the data from the study is later deleted. Jade expresses interest in applying for a nursing bursary, to which Marty mocks her. Ruby tells Jan about her involvement with Dani, to which Jan reprimands her. Ruby notifies Dani that her the police have been informed of her actions, and Ruby later attends a paramedic support group with Iain, where she talks about the issue.\n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1132\n| EpisodeNumber2=39\n| RTitle=Episode 39<ref name=\"33x39\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 39|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m00062zr|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writers: Johanne McAndrew, Elliot Hope; Director: Fiona Walton; Producer: Dafydd Llewelyn|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=15 June 2019}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Johanne McAndrew and Elliot Hope \n| DirectedBy= Fiona Walton\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|6|15|df=y}}\n| Viewers=4.48\n| ShortSummary= Connie returns from the conference to find that Ciaran has been working in her office. Jacob catches Jet dealing drugs outside of Omo's house, and when she blocks the doorway, he forces entry and knocks her over. Both Omo and Jet are taken to the hospital, where Omo vomits on the floor. Jacob secretly browses Omo's medical records, where he learns she has pancreatic cancer. Dylan informs him that she is not strong enough for chemotherapy, and that she has up to a couple of months to live. Jacob has Omo's medication tested at the pharmacy, and it is revealed that Jet has been selling her morphine and swapping it. Archie visits Connie in her office, and after she leaves, Connie closes the blinds and takes diazepam. \n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1133\n| EpisodeNumber2=40\n| RTitle=Episode 40<ref name=\"33x40\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 40|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m00069hx|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writer: Claire Miller; Director: Nimer Rashed; Producer: Sean Gleeson|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=22 June 2019}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Claire Miller\n| DirectedBy= Nimer Rashed\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|6|22|df=y}}\n| Viewers=4.33\n| ShortSummary= On her way to work, Duffy assesses the condition of a girl hit by a bus. David assesses Marty and Jade on their ability of taking care of adults with minor illnesses. Jacob discovers blood in Omo's bag, and insists on taking her into hospital. Dylan informs her that her pancreatic tumour is pushing against the wall of her stomach; she refuses treatment but Jacob later convinces her otherwise. Charlie informs the department that although Duffy is not leaving, she will no longer be doing any clinical tasks.  \n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1134\n| EpisodeNumber2=41\n| RTitle=Episode 41<ref name=\"33x41\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 41|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m0006hk1|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writer: Rachel Paterson; Director: Julie Edwards; Producer: Kirsty Lane|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=29 June 2019}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Rachel Paterson\n| DirectedBy= Julie Edwards\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|6|29|df=y}}\n| Viewers=3.99\n| ShortSummary= Jade catches Jacob unsuccessfully trying to find details about his father on Omo's medical records; Omo's carer finds Omo collapsed on the floor and she calls for Jacob's help. Ruby explains to Jacob that Omo has a suspected neck-of-femur fracture. Dylan informs Jacob that any procedures on Omo would be too invasive, but he convinces Dylan to allow more time. Omo directs Jacob to a piece of paper at the back of her bible with his father's name on, but tells him to only look when she is dead. Jacob has Omo taken home in the back of an ambulance, and lies next to her in bed, reading [[John 14]] to her. When Omo dies, he takes the name of his father and burns the page rather than looking at it.\n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1135\n| EpisodeNumber2=42\n| RTitle=Episode 42<ref name=\"33x42\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 42|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m0006pdw|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writer: Isla Gray; Director: Julie Edwards; Producer: Kirsty Lane|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=13 July 2019}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Isla Gray\n| DirectedBy= Julie Edwards\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|7|13|df=y}}\n| Viewers=4.24\n| ShortSummary= As they pass the staffroom, Iain and Ruby learn that Frankie, a former patient of Iain's, has gone missing. Marty gets awarded the Wyvern Nurse Bursary, to Jade's annoyance. Iain visits Frankie's mother, and sees a photo of Frankie at a soft play area, which he visits and finds her. Jade complains to David that with her deadness, she has faced more difficulties than Marty, and reveals that she ultimately did not apply for the bursary. Jade sees Marty's phone calling, and answers to his dad, telling him about the award. When his father Graham arrives, David accidentally mentions Marty's sexuality being a difficult, and it is revealed that Marty is not [[coming out|out as gay]] to his parents. When Graham asks what David meant about his sexuality, Jade interrupts and says that she is Marty's girlfriend.\n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1136\n| EpisodeNumber2=43\n| RTitle=Episode 43<ref name=\"33x43\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 43|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m0006wft|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writer: Dana Fainaru; Director: Piotr Szkopiak; Producer: Sean Gleeson|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=20 July 2019}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Dana Fainaru\n| DirectedBy= Piotr Szkopiak\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|7|20|df=y}}\n| Viewers= 4.22\n| ShortSummary= Connie awakens in her office, and on her way home, she almost gets hit by a motorcycle, so hides in her office. She then receives an email from Hanssen, asking her to respect the board's decision about hiring Ciaran; she dismisses it and takes a diazepam tablet. Connie appears in resus and fills a syringe with local anaesthetic, as a patient begins to shout in pain \u2013 Archie discovers her cannula is kinked, and Connie suggests flushing it with saline. When Duffy arrives, Connie asks her to flush the cannula; while Duffy is not supposed to do clinical tasks, she agrees. Connie tells her that the saline syringe is closest to her. One patient begins to have a seizure and a cardiac arrest, as the other shouts in pain at a wound being sutured; Connie then realises the mistake she has made by not labelling the syringes. \n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1137\n| EpisodeNumber2=44\n| RTitle=Episode 44<ref name=\"33x44\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 44|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m00077nf|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writers: Nick Fisher, Dana Fainaru; Director: Piotr Szkopiak; Producer: Sean Gleeson|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=27 July 2019}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Nick Fisher and Dana Fainaru\n| DirectedBy= Piotr Szkopiak\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|7|27|df=y}}\n| Viewers= 4.28\n| ShortSummary= Charlie visits Connie in her office, and she shows him her letter of resignation. Archie tells Will that the mixup was Connie's fault, but he suggests she needs proof. Rosa Cadenas, the new porter, introduces herself to David and later fixes his car. After taking a diazepam tablet, Connie finds the syringes from the accident, and disposes of them. Connie asks Duffy what she remembers of the incident, and asks if she checked the labels, leaving Duffy questioning her memory. Duffy packs her belongings and apologises to Connie for her mistake, and although Connie urges her to stay, she insists on leaving. Archie and Ciaran overhear, and Ciaran accuses her of \"throwing Duffy under the bus in cold blood\", leaving Connie worried.\n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1138\n| EpisodeNumber2=45\n| RTitle=Episode 45<ref name=\"33x45\">{{cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/tv-programme/e/h626z7/casualty--series-33-episode-45/|title=Series 33 \u2013 Episode 45|work=[[Radio Times]]|accessdate=24 July 2019}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Colin Bytheway\n| DirectedBy= James Bryce\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|8|3|df=y}}\n| Viewers= 4.49\n| ShortSummary= Marty's mother Bibi insists Graham that Jade is not right for Marty, and then collapses. Dylan informs Bibi that her heart monitor is showing [[heart block]]. Speaking to Marty, Bibi tells him that she knows he is gay, and has known for years. Will tells Archie that he saw Connie taking diazepam in her office. Marty comes out as gay to his father, who takes it negatively and suggests that they no longer see each other. Archie goes into Connie's office, and finds the diazepam. Ciaran enters her office and demands to search her desk for diazepam, but does not find it as she has hidden it in her handbag.\n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1139\n| EpisodeNumber2=46\n| RTitle=Episode 46<ref name=\"33x46\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/tv-programme/e/h7s8v5/casualty--series-33-episode-46/|title=Series 33 \u2013 Episode 46|website=Radio Times|language=en|access-date=3 August 2019}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Hilary Frankland, Patrick Homes & Katie Douglas\n| DirectedBy= Alex Jacob\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|8|10|df=y}}\n| Viewers= 4.94\n| ShortSummary= '''Day one'''\n\nConnie learns that all benzodiazepine prescriptions must be double-signed due to an initiative from Hanssen. She takes over the inquiry and requests the ED's script records for the last three months. Ciaran is later called into Connie's office, where Hanssen explains that a staff member has been prescribing three times as many benzodiazepines as other colleagues. Ciaran blames Connie, but Hanssen informs him that the hospital will not be renewing his contract. Before leaving, Ciaran tells Archie that she needs to continue pursuing Connie. New emergency care assistant Siobhan assists Iain on a callout to a road traffic collision, but it soon emerges that she is an alcoholic, and has been drinking while on duty. Gem expresses her desire to join Rash while he is travelling, and Iain gives her the money she needs to leave Holby. \n\n'''Day two'''\n\nIn a multi-storey car park, Duffy reverses her car as a girl named Shanti runs out behind it and falls to the ground. Shanti insists she has a broken arm, but Duffy knows she is lying to scam vulnerable people. Connie writes herself a prescription for diazepam, and goes to a local pharmacy to collect it. Archie follows Connie and confronts her, but they soon become caught up in a hostage situation, as the pharmacist is held at knifepoint by a drug addict, who Connie recognises as her daughter's former babysitter, Michelle. Connie attempts to defuse the situation, but Archie is stabbed. She is stabilised at the hospital. Connie tells Charlie about her drug addiction and how she let Duffy take the blame for her mistake. Charlie is disgusted with her and tells her to go.\n\n''Note'': this was a feature length episode. It was originally meant to be two singular episodes, but was merged into one.\n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0bg73yz ''Casualty'' Series 33] at [[BBC Online]]\n* [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0096555/episodes?season=33&ref_=tt_eps_sn_33 ''Casualty'' series 33] at the [[Internet Movie Database]]\n\n{{Holby|Casualty}}\n\n[[Category:Casualty (TV series) episodes| ]]\n[[Category:2018 British television seasons]]\n[[Category:2019 British television seasons]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Short description|Thirty-third series of Casualty}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox television season\n| image            =\n| caption          = \n| season_number    = 33\n| bgcolour         = #80FF8A\n| country          = [[United Kingdom]]\n| network          = {{Plainlist|[[BBC One]]\n*[[BBC One HD]]}}\n| first_aired      = {{start date|2018|08|11|df=y}}\n| last_aired       = {{end date|2019|08|10|df=y}}\n| num_episodes     = 46<!--Number of episodes aired, not planned for series-->\n| episode_list     = List of Casualty episodes\n}}\nThe '''thirty-third series''' of the British [[medical drama]] [[television series]] ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]'' began airing on [[BBC One]] in the United Kingdom on 11 August 2018, one week after the end of the previous series. The series consisted of 46 episodes. Lucy Raffety continues her role as [[series producer]], while Simon Harper continues his role as the show's [[executive producer]]. Sixteen regular cast members reprised their roles from the [[Casualty (series 32)|previous series]]. The series, which is billed as \"The Year of the Paramedic\", begins with a motorway collision stunt sequence, and features a [[CasualtyXHolby|crossover episode]] with spin-off series, ''[[Holby City]]''. This series featured the departures of six cast members, including [[Amanda Mealing]] as [[Connie Beauchamp]], Azuka Oforka as [[Louise Tyler]] and [[Chelsea Halfpenny]] as [[Alicia Munroe]]. Four new regular cast members also joined the series, while two actors began appearing in a recurring capacity.\n\n== Cast ==\n=== Overview ===\nThe thirty-third series of ''Casualty'' features a cast of characters working in the emergency department of [[Holby City Hospital]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/casualty-celebrates-1000-episodes-30-8280563|title=Casualty celebrates 1,000 episodes, 30 years and 2,500 gallons of fake blood|last=Pryer|first=Emma|date=25 June 2016|publisher=Daily Mirror|accessdate=11 August 2016}}</ref> The majority of the cast from the [[Casualty (series 32)|previous series]] continue to appear in this series. [[Amanda Mealing]] appears as clinical lead and [[Consultant (medicine)|consultant]] in [[emergency medicine]] [[Connie Beauchamp]], while [[William Beck (actor)|William Beck]], [[George Rainsford (actor)|George Rainsford]] and [[Jaye Griffiths]] portray consultants [[Dylan Keogh]], [[Ethan Hardy]], and [[Elle Gardner]] respectively. [[Chelsea Halfpenny]] portrays [[specialty registrar]] [[Alicia Munroe]], who later specialises in [[pediatric emergency medicine]]. [[Neet Mohan]] appears as [[Foundation doctor|F1 doctor]] [[Rash Masum]], while [[Derek Thompson (actor)|Derek Thompson]] stars as [[Charlie Fairhead]], the [[clinical nurse manager]], senior [[charge nurse]] and [[emergency nurse practitioner]]. [[Cathy Shipton]] appears as [[Lisa \"Duffy\" Duffin]], a [[Nursing sister|sister]] and [[midwife]]. [[Charles Venn]] portrays senior [[staff nurse]] [[Jacob Masters]], while Azuka Oforka features as staff nurse [[Louise Tyler]], who is later promoted to senior staff nurse. [[Amanda Henderson]] and [[Jason Durr]] play staff nurses [[Robyn Miller (Casualty)|Robyn Miller]] and [[David Hide]]. [[Charlotte Salt]], [[Michael Stevenson (actor)|Michael Stevenson]] and [[Maddy Hill]] portray [[paramedics]] [[Sam Nicholls]], [[Iain Dean]], and [[Ruby Spark]] respectively. [[Tony Marshall (actor)|Tony Marshall]] stars as [[receptionist]] [[Noel Garcia]]. Additionally, four cast members feature on the series in a recurring capacity: [[Rebecca Ryan]] features as [[Porter (carrier)|porter]] [[Gemma Dean]]; Kai Thorne portrays [[Blake Gardner]]; Joe Gaminara appears as F1 doctor [[Eddie McAllister]]; and [[Di Botcher]] plays operational duty manager and paramedic [[Jan Jenning]].<ref name=\"33x01\"/><ref name=\"33x02\"/><ref name=\"Trailer\">{{cite news |last1=Alexander |first1=Susannah |title=Casualty teases a new era in stunning new trailer after shock death changes everything |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/news/a863742/casualty-new-trailer-new-era-after-shock-death/ |accessdate=12 August 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=12 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Shaheen Jafargholi 2016.jpg|150px|thumb|right|[[Shaheen Jafargholi]] joined the cast as student nurse [[Marty Kirkby]] in episode 13.]]\nIn the opening episode of the series, Sam is killed off after succumbing to injuries sustained in a motorway collision. Salt, who had returned during the previous series, decided to leave again, but was shocked to discover her character would die. She was glad that her departure was kept hidden and felt it had a greater impact.<ref name=\"Sam\">{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty star Charlotte Salt reacts to Sam Nicholls's shock exit |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/feature/a863654/casualty-catch-up-charlotte-salt-sam-nicholls-shock-exit/ |accessdate=12 August 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=11 August 2018}}</ref> Gaminara makes his last appearance in episode 3 after pleading guilty to attacking Alicia.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Haasler |first1=Sue |title=Casualty review with spoilers: Alicia in at the deep end |url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/08/25/casualty-review-with-spoilers-alicia-in-at-the-deep-end-7870891/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |date=25 August 2018}}</ref> Halfpenny opted to leave her role as Alicia in 2018 after deciding to pursue other roles. Alicia departs in episode 20.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Reilly |first1=Elaine |title=Casualty interview: Chelsea Halfpenny reveals why she's leaving Casualty |url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/news/casualty-interview-chelsea-halfpenny-reveals-shes-bowing-casualty-564801/ |accessdate=26 January 2019 |work=[[What's on TV]] |date=15 January 2019}}</ref> Oforka also chose to leave her role as Louise, having appeared in the show since [[Casualty (series 26)|series 26]]. The character's exit was not announced beforehand and Louise leaves in episode 24 after an ongoing financial struggle.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty star Azuka Oforka bows out from her role as Louise Tyler |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a26323115/casualty-spoilers-azuka-oforka-louise-tyler-exit/ |accessdate=17 February 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=16 February 2019}}</ref> Oforka thanked fans for their support on social network [[Twitter]] and expressed her delight at working on the drama.<ref>{{cite tweet|last=Oforka|first=Azuka|user=AzukaOforka|number=1096897184056991744|date=16 February 2019|title=Aww guys I was only meant to be in 3 episodes!! But after 7 years that's a wrap on my time in #Casualty and Louise exits the way she entered....tottering down the ambulance run!! Thank you so much for your love, support and kind words, it means a lot|accessdate=17 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|last=Oforka|first=Azuka|user=AzukaOforka|number=1096897961047613440|date=16 February 2019|title=So much love for my Casualty family, past and present. We work really really hard, but laugh even harder. It was rare for a day to pass where I didn't fall to the floor in hysterics crying tears of laughter (Sorry Make Up Department!) It's the giggles I'll miss the most|accessdate=17 February 2019}}</ref> Griffiths' exit from the series was announced on 4 May 2019;<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty confirms exit for Elle Gardner as she drops a bombshell on Connie |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a27352648/casualty-spoilers-elle-gardner-exit-confirmed/ |accessdate=6 August 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=4 May 2019}}</ref> her character left in episode 36.<ref>{{cite news |last1=McIntyre |first1=Charlotte |title=Casualty spoilers: Viewers in tears over Elle Gardner and Connie's heartbreaking goodbye |url=https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/1132153/Casualty-spoilers-Elle-Gardner-exit-Connie-Beauchamp-tears-goodbye-Jaye-Griffith-BBC |accessdate=6 August 2019 |work=[[Daily Express]] |date=25 May 2019}}</ref> Mohan took a four-month break from the series in 2019 and his character departed in episode 32 after deciding to travel the globe.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty airs exit scenes for Rash Masum as Neet Mohan takes a break from the show |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a27151727/casualty-spoilers-rash-masum-neet-mohan-exit-temporary/ |accessdate=6 August 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=20 April 2019}}</ref> Rash returns during the [[Casualty (series 34)|following series]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Casualty |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/proginfo/2019/34/casualty |accessdate=6 August 2019 |work=[[BBC Media Centre]]}}</ref> Mealing's break from the show was announced on 15 April 2019 after the actress finished filming days earlier. A show spokesperson confirmed that Connie would return in the \"autumn\", during the following series.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Edwards |first1=Chris |title=Casualty confirms Amanda Mealing is taking a break from her role as Connie Beauchamp |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a27153258/casualty-amanda-mealing-taking-break-connie-beauchamp-role/ |accessdate=6 August 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=15 April 2019}}</ref> Connie departs in the season finale at the conclusion of her story about [[posttraumatic stress disorder]] and [[drug addiction]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Exclusive: Casualty star Amanda Mealing backs Connie and Jacob reunion \u2013 and reveals why they had to split |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a28619270/casualty-amanda-mealing-connie-jacob-reunion/ |accessdate=6 August 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=6 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 August 2018, Sophie Dainty of ''[[Digital Spy]]'' reported that former ''[[EastEnders]]'' actor [[Shaheen Jafargholi]] had joined the cast as new nurse, [[Marty Kirkby]].<ref name=\"Shaheen\">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/news/a862906/casualty-spoilers-eastenders-shaheen-jafargholi-cast-nurse-marty/|title=Exclusive: Former EastEnders star Shaheen Jafargholi is joining Casualty as new nurse Marty|last=Dainty|first=Sophie|date=1 August 2018|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]]|accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref> Series producer Lucy Raffety revealed on 15 August 2018 that actress Gabriella Leon would join the show alongside Jafargholi, playing student nurse [[Jade Lovell]].<ref name=\"Raffety int\">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/feature/a864036/casualty-spoilers-secrets-show-boss-lucy-raffety/|title=Exclusive: Casualty: 15 HUGE secrets and spoilers from the show's boss Lucy Raffety|last=Dainty|first=Sophie|date=15 August 2018|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]]|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref> Jade first appears in episode 12, originally broadcast on 3 November 2018, while Marty first appears in episode 13, originally broadcast on 17 November 2018.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Edwards |first1=Chris |title=Casualty offers first look as former EastEnders star Shaheen Jafargholi joins as Marty |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/news/a869773/casualty-first-look-eastenders-shaheen-jafargholi-marty/ |accessdate=1 November 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=1 November 2018}}</ref> Raffety also announced plans to introduce new doctors during this series.<ref name=\"Raffety int\"/> [[Genesis Lynea]] and Jack Nolan were later cast as registrars Archie Hudson and Will Noble.<ref name=\"Dainty spring\">{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty reveals 8 huge spoilers in the show's explosive spring trailer |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a26750118/casualty-spoilers-spring-trailer-2019/ |accessdate=16 March 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=7 March 2019}}</ref> Archie is characterised as \"bold, bolshy and extremely confident\", while Will is billed as unfazed by Archie's personality.<ref name=\"Dainty spring\"/> Department troubleshooter Ciaran Coulson ([[Rick Warden]]) is introduced in episode 37 as part of the semi-regular cast. He is created as an unlikeable character and rival to Connie, who tries to improve the ED after they fail to meet targets.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Ellis |first1=Sarah |title=Clash of the Titans! |journal=[[Inside Soap]] |date=1-7 June 2019 |volume=2019 |issue=22 |pages=48\u201349}}</ref> Raffety announced on 31 May 2019 that [[Jacey Sall\u00e9s]] would join the cast as porter [[Rosa Cadenas]] during the series and feature in an \"interesting story\" with David.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Reilly |first1=Elaine |title=Connie's dramatic exit! Plus more massive Casualty spoilers revealed!|url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/news/tv-times-exclusive-coming-soon-casualty-580601/ |accessdate=29 July 2019 |work=[[What's on TV]] |date=31 May 2019}}</ref> Rosa first appears in episode 44.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Haasler |first1=Sue |title=7 Casualty spoilers: How far will Connie go to save her job? |url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/07/27/7-casualty-spoilers-how-far-will-connie-go-to-save-her-job-10444867/ |accessdate=29 July 2019 |work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |date=27 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe series features several recurring characters and multiple guest stars. It was announced on 21 June 2018 that actress [[Sharon Gless]] would reprise her guest role as [[neurosurgeon]] [[Zsa Zsa Harper-Jenkinson]] in the series.<ref name=\"Gless\">{{Cite tweet|number=1009765374408052737|user=BBCCasualty|title=EXCITING NEWS! Zsa Zsa is back! @SharonGless will return as the sharp-witted Brain Surgeon later in the year. #Casualty|date=21 June 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018}}</ref> Zsa Zsa appears in episode 9.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Reilly |first1=Elaine |title=Casualty guest star Sharon Gless: 'Connie meets her match in Zsa Zsa!' |url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/casualty/casualty-news/casualty-guest-star-sharon-gless-connie-meets-match-in-zsa-zsa-553381/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=[[What's on TV]] |date=9 October 2018}}</ref> In August, it was confirmed that [[Ellen Thomas (actress)|Ellen Thomas]] would be playing Jacob's mother Omo Masters from September 2018.<ref>{{cite journal|date=11\u201317 August 2018|title=In and out|journal=[[Inside Soap]]|issue=32|page=92}}</ref> Thomas appears in episodes 6 and 8 respectively.<ref name=\"33x06\"/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Reilly |first1=Elaine |title=Exclusive! Charles Venn having 'fantastic' time on Strictly and Casualty |url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/news/exclusive-charles-venn-talks-strictly-casualty-552740/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=[[What's on TV]] |date=5 October 2018}}</ref> In February 2019, it was confirmed that Thomas had reprised the role for another stint exploring Jacob's backstory,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty is bringing back EastEnders star Ellen Thomas for huge new Jacob story |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a26195957/casualty-spoilers-eastenders-ellen-thomas-jacob-omo-story/ |accessdate=6 February 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=6 February 2019}}</ref> and she appears between episode 36 and 41, where the character was killed off.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Reilly |first1=Elaine |title=Charles Venn reveals why new Casualty storylines 'have been a long time coming' |url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/news/charles-venn-reveals-new-casualty-storylines-long-time-coming-579451/ |accessdate=6 August 2019 |work=[[What's on TV]] |date=21 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Brown |first1=David |title=Who is Casualty's Ellen Thomas? All you need to know about the star playing Jacob's mum Omo |url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/2019-06-29/who-is-casualtys-ellen-thomas-all-you-need-to-know-about-the-star-playing-jacobs-mum-omo/ |accessdate=6 August 2019 |work=[[Radio Times]] |date=29 June 2019}}</ref> Episode one features the first appearance of Max Parker as Alasdair \"Base\" Newman, a drug addict who Iain befriends.<ref name=\"33x01\"/> Parker reappears from episode five as part of the recurring cast,<ref>{{cite news |title=Casaulty spoilers: It's war! Ciara comes between Dylan and David |url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/events/casualty-spoilers-war-ciara-comes-dylan-david/ |accessdate=2 December 2018 |work=[[What's on TV]]}}</ref> and departs in episode 22 when his character is killed off.<ref name=\"Ross\">{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty: Has Iain killed Ross? 7 new spoilers after that shocking cliffhanger |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a26038501/casualty-iain-ross-spoilers/ |accessdate=3 February 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=26 January 2017}}</ref> Base's drug dealer, Ross West (Chris Gordon), also appears in the series across five episodes between episode 5 and episode 22. In his final episode, Ross is revealed to be Jan's son.<ref name=\"Ross\"/> The same storyline also sees the reappearance of DC Kate Wilkinson (Amy Noble) in episode 22, a character who has appeared on-off since [[Casualty (series 30)|series 30]].<ref name=\"33x22\"/>\n\n[[Belinda Stewart-Wilson]] rejoins the recurring cast as Ciara Cassidy, Dylan's alcoholic friend, in episode 2, following her appearance in the previous series.<ref>{{cite news |title=Casualty spoilers: Sam Nicholls dead! Iain sacked? |url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/events/casualty-spoilers-sam-nicholls-dead-iain-sacked/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=[[What's on TV]]}}</ref> [[Gyuri Sarossy]] is later introduced as Ciara's husband, Joel Dunns, in episode 5.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Reilly |first1=Elaine |title=Casualty interview! William Beck: 'Dylan and Ciara's story is the definition of tragedy' |url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/casualty/casualty-interview-william-beck-dylan-ciaras-story-definition-tragedy-550807/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=[[What's on TV]] |date=18 September 2018}}</ref> Both characters depart in episode 14.<ref name=\"33x14\"/> Accredited actor [[Clive Wood]] makes his first appearance as Duffy's \"childhood sweetheart\", Bill Crowthers, in episode 3.<ref name=\"33x03\"/> Dainty confirmed that Wood would feature prominently in Duffy's new storyline.<ref name=\"Spoilers\"/> Bill's daughter, Rachael Crowthers (Jennifer Hulman), was later introduced, appearing in episodes 7 and 16.<ref name=\"33x07\"/><ref name=\"33x16\"/> Rash's childhood friend, Jamila Vani (Sujaya Dasgupta), appears between episode 7 and episode 11.<ref name=\"33x07\"/><ref name=\"33x11\"/> Dylan's father, Brian Carroll ([[Matthew Marsh (actor)|Matthew Marsh]]), appears in episode 9, having last featured in [[Casualty (series 30)|series 30]].<ref name=\"Spoilers\">{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty autumn spoilers: 7 big storylines hitting your screens very soon |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/feature/a867171/casualty-autumn-spoilers-2018/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=29 September 2018}}</ref> [[Gareth David-Lloyd]] appears as Jade's boss, Joshua Bowers, in episode 12.<ref name=\"33x12\"/> The character, billed as a \"dishy doctor\", returns from episode 15 as a love interest for Marty,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty: 7 of the biggest storylines coming your way this Christmas |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a871735/casualty-christmas-storylines-revealed/ |accessdate=9 December 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=30 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Casualty spoilers: Duffy's affair exposed! |url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/events/casualty-spoilers-duffys-affair-exposed/ |accessdate=9 December 2018 |work=[[What's on TV]]}}</ref> but leaves in episode 20.<ref name=\"33x20\"/> Actor [[Paul Barber (actor)|Paul Barber]] joined the recurring cast in episode 13 as Ernest Maxwell, a homeless man involved in a storyline with Louise.<ref name=\"33x13\"/><ref>{{cite news |title=Casualty spoilers: Ian Dean takes a big risk! |url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/events/casualty-iain-dean-risk/ |accessdate=3 February 2019 |work=[[What's on TV]]}}</ref> The character is killed-off in episode 23 as the storyline continues, emotionally impacting Louise.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty: Who attacked Connie? 7 big theories and questions after the shock cliffhanger |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a26252953/casualty-catch-up-who-attacked-connie/ |accessdate=16 February 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=9 February 2019}}</ref> [[Sian Reeves]] reprised her role as Kim Harrison, the mother of Iain and Gem, in episode 24 and 27.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty is bringing back former Emmerdale star Sian Reeves for the latest twist in Iain's story |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a26323172/casualty-spoilers-iain-dean-mum-kim-sian-reeves/ |accessdate=16 March 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=13 February 2019}}</ref> Georgia Hughes joined the recurring cast as Dani Mallison in episode 27 and features in a storyline with Ruby.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty lines up huge new story for Ruby Spark as she befriends newcomer Dani |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a26724388/casualty-spoilers-ruby-sparks-new-story-dani/ |accessdate=7 March 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=6 March 2019}}</ref> Harry Gilby also joined the recurring cast as Toby Williams in episode 29 and features in an ongoing story with Will.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty is lining up a heartbreaking story for new doctor Will Noble |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a26975795/casualty-spoilers-will-noble-tragic-story-jack-nolan-debut/ |accessdate=7 April 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=30 March 2019}}</ref> Towards the end of the series, Marty's parents, Bibi Kirkby (Badria Timimi) and Graham Kirkby ([[Philip Wright (actor)|Philip Wright]]), were introduced as part of a story exploring Marty [[coming out]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=7 huge Casualty spoilers for this week |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a28565245/casualty-spoilers-marty-devastated-connie-exposed/ |accessdate=6 August 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=1 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{col begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n\n=== Main characters ===\n* [[William Beck (actor)|William Beck]] as [[Dylan Keogh]]\n* [[Jason Durr]] as [[David Hide]]\n* [[Jaye Griffiths]] as [[Elle Gardner]]\n* [[Chelsea Halfpenny]] as [[Alicia Munroe]]\n* [[Amanda Henderson]] as [[Robyn Miller (Casualty)|Robyn Miller]]\n* [[Maddy Hill]] as [[Ruby Spark]]\n* [[Shaheen Jafargholi]] as [[Marty Kirkby]]\n* Gabriella Leon as [[Jade Lovall]]\n* [[Genesis Lynea]] as [[Archie Hudson]]\n* [[Tony Marshall (actor)|Tony Marshall]] as [[Noel Garcia]]\n* [[Amanda Mealing]] as [[Connie Beauchamp]]\n* [[Neet Mohan]] as [[Rash Masum]]\n* Jack Nolan as [[Will Noble]]\n* Azuka Oforka as [[Louise Tyler]]\n* [[George Rainsford (actor)|George Rainsford]] as [[Ethan Hardy]]\n* [[Rebecca Ryan]] as [[Gemma Dean]]\n* [[Charlotte Salt]] as [[Sam Nicholls]]\n* [[Cathy Shipton]] as [[Lisa \"Duffy\" Duffin]]\n* [[Michael Stevenson (actor)|Michael Stevenson]] as [[Iain Dean]]\n* [[Derek Thompson (actor)|Derek Thompson]] as [[Charlie Fairhead]]\n* [[Charles Venn]] as [[Jacob Masters]]\n\n{{col-3}}\n\n=== Recurring characters ===\n* [[Paul Barber (actor)|Paul Barber]] as Ernest Maxwell\n* [[Di Botcher]] as [[Jan Jenning]]\n* [[Gareth David-Lloyd]] as Joshua Bowers\n* Joe Gaminara as [[Eddie McAllister]]\n* Harry Gilby as Toby Williams\n* Chris Gordon as Ross West\n* Georgia Hughes as Dani Mallison\n* [[Rebecca Ryan]] as [[Gemma Dean]]\n* Max Parker as Alasdair \"Base\" Newman\n* [[Jacey Sall\u00e9s]] as [[Rosa Cadenas]]\n* [[Gyuri Sarossy]] as Joel Dunns\n* [[Belinda Stewart-Wilson]] as Ciara Cassidy\n* Kai Thorne as [[Blake Gardner]]\n* [[Rick Warden]] as [[Ciaran Coulson]]\n* [[Clive Wood]] as Bill Crowthers\n\n{{col-3}}\n\n=== Guest characters ===\n* [[Camilla Arfwedson]] as [[Zosia Self]]\n* [[Bob Barrett (actor)|Bob Barrett]] as [[Sacha Levy]]\n* Francesca Barrett as Beka Levy\n* Sujaya Dasgupta as Jamila Vani\n* [[Sharon Gless]] as [[Zsa Zsa Harper-Jenkinson]]\n* Marcus Griffiths as [[Xavier Duval]]\n* [[Guy Henry (actor)|Guy Henry]] as [[Henrik Hanssen]]\n* Jennifer Hulman as Rachael Crowthers\n* Nic Jackman as Cameron Dunn\n* [[Jaye Jacobs]] as [[Donna Jackson]]\n* Naomi Katiyo as Darla Johnstone\n* [[Rosie Marcel]] as [[Jac Naylor]]\n* [[Matthew Marsh (actor)|Matthew Marsh]] as Brian Carroll\n* Amy Noble as DCI Wilkinson\n* [[Belinda Owusu]] as [[Nicky McKendrick]]\n* [[Hugh Quarshie]] as [[Ric Griffin]]\n* [[Ellen Thomas (actress)|Ellen Thomas]] as Omo Masters\n* Badria Timimi as Bibi Kirkby\n* [[Sian Reeves]] as Kim Harrison\n* [[Catherine Russell (actress)|Catherine Russell]] as [[Serena Campbell]]\n* [[Alex Walkinshaw]] as [[Adrian \"Fletch\" Fletcher]]\n* [[Kaye Wragg]] as [[Essie Di Lucca]]\n* [[Philip Wright (actor)|Philip Wright]] as Graham Kirkby\n{{col end}}\n\n== Production ==\nThe thirty-third series will consist of 47 episodes.<ref name=\"33x01\"/> Lucy Raffety continues her role as [[series producer]] while Simon Harper remains as the [[executive producer]].<ref name=\"X\"/> [[Kate Oates]] became the show's senior executive producer from October 2018,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/eastenders/news/a863452/eastenders-casualty-holby-city-new-producer-kate-oates/|title=EastEnders confirms new boss as Kate Oates takes over from John Yorke in top job|last=Dainty|first=Sophie|date=8 August 2018|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]]|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref> and was promoted to Head of Continuing Drama six months later.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mehmedova |first1=Filiz |title=EastEnders boss Kate Oates lands a new role with the BBC \u2013 and will be in charge of more shows |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/eastenders/a27150376/eastenders-boss-kate-oates-new-role-with-the-bbc/ |accessdate=16 April 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=15 April 2019}}</ref> Raffety's resignation from her position was announced on 16 April 2019.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mehmedova |first1=Filiz |title=Casualty is searching for a new producer - and Holby City has a new boss |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a27164855/casualty-new-producer-holby-city-new-boss/ |accessdate=17 April 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=16 April 2019}}</ref> Raffety confirmed that there would be a series 33 in an interview with ''[[TVTimes]]'', where she billed the series as the \"Year of the Paramedic\".<ref name=\"Bullimore\">{{cite journal|last1=Bullimore|first1=Emma|title=Coming soon... Casualty 2018|journal=[[TV Times]]|date=17-23 March 2018|pages=4\u20135}}</ref> In preparation for the series, two new paramedic characters were introduced to the drama.<ref name=\"Bullimore\"/>\n\nIt was announced on 24 July 2018 that the series would begin on 11 August 2018 with an episode described as \"one of [the] biggest episodes in the show's history.\"<ref name=\"Dainty\">{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty will kick off new series with one of the biggest episodes in show's history |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/news/a862300/casualty-spoilers-explosion-stunt-new-series/ |accessdate=24 July 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=24 July 2018}}</ref> It was previously revealed, in May 2018, that the show was filming scenes which would feature a motorway crash and a [[petrol tanker]] turning on its side.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty is lining up a shocking explosion stunt later this year |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/news/a856704/casualty-spoilers-shock-explosion-stunt/ |accessdate=24 July 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=9 May 2018}}</ref> Sophie Dainty of entertainment website ''[[Digital Spy]]'' reported that there would be an explosion, which would leave one main character's life \"hanging in the balance\".<ref name=\"Dainty\"/> An official statement from the show stated that the ED's paramedic crew would \"face their darkest day\" in the episode.<ref name=\"Dainty\"/> Charlotte Salt, who portrays Sam Nicholls, told Elaine Reilly of ''[[What's on TV]]'' that the episodes were filmed at night over two weeks with night shoots lasting over 13 hours. On the atmosphere on-set while filming, she commented, \"there's a certain buzz in the air...\"<ref name=\"Salt\">{{cite news |last1=Reilly |first1=Elaine |title=Charlotte Salt: 'Jan is the third point to Sam and Iain's triangle' |url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/casualty/casualty-news/charlotte-salt-jan-third-point-sam-iains-triangle-casualty-534973/ |accessdate=24 July 2018 |work=[[What's on TV]] |date=21 May 2018}}</ref> The episode sees Sam die after suffering a fatal bleed from the crash, which sparks a new story for Iain as he struggles to cope with his grief.<ref name=\"Sam\"/> A show trailer, released on 12 August, teased \"a new era\" for the hospital following Sam's death. The trailer previewed Iain's guilt, the appearances of Zsa Zsa and Omo, Eddie facing trial for Alicia's rape, and upsetting scenes for Charlie and Duffy.<ref name=\"Trailer\"/> On 16 November 2018, it was revealed via ''Casualty''{{'s}} official [[Instagram]] page that the show would be receiving a new set of titles.<ref name=\"New Titles\">{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty is getting an exciting new look and opening titles \u2013 and you can preview it here |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/news/a870749/casualty-is-getting-an-exciting-new-look-and-opening-titles-and-you-can-preview-it-here/ |accessdate=16 November 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=19 November 2018}}</ref> The revamp came into effect from episode 13, which aired on 17 November 2018,<ref name=\"33x13\"/> replacing the show's former titles, which were introduced back in [[Casualty (series 31)|series 31]].<ref name=\"New Titles\"/>\n\n=== Crossovers ===\nThis series features [[crossover (fiction)|crossover]] events with ''Holby City''{{'s}} sister show ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]''.<ref name=\"Raffety\"/> In August 2018, Raffety told Dainty (''Digital Spy'') that Harper enjoys the crossover events between the two dramas and wanted to produce more. She also teased some \"extremely exciting crossovers\" within the series.<ref name=\"Raffety\">{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Casualty: 15 HUGE secrets and spoilers from the show's boss Lucy Raffety |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/casualty/a864036/casualty-spoilers-secrets-show-boss-lucy-raffety/ |accessdate=21 February 2019 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=15 August 2018}}</ref> In a December 2018 interview with Dainty, Harper promised further crossovers between ''Holby City'' and ''Casualty'', and teased an \"exciting\" event to be aired in spring 2019.<ref name=\"Anniversary\">{{cite news |last1=Dainty |first1=Sophie |title=Holby City's 20th anniversary \u2013 spoilers, returns and everything else you need to know |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/holby-city/a25468516/holby-city-spoilers-20th-anniversary/ |accessdate=11 December 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=11 December 2018}}</ref> ''Holby City'' cast member [[Alex Walkinshaw]] ([[Adrian \"Fletch\" Fletcher]]), who appeared in ''Casualty'' between 2012 and 2014, makes a crossover appearance in episode 31.<ref name=\"33x31\"/>\n\n[[File:Guy Henry (cropped).jpg|190px|thumb|right|''Holby City'' actor [[Guy Henry (actor)|Guy Henry]] appears as [[Henrik Hanssen]] in the crossover event, and then again in the series finale.]]\nOn 15 February 2019, it was announced that ''Casualty'' would crossover with spin-off series ''[[Holby City]]'' for two episodes, billed as \"[[CasualtyXHolby]]\", in March as part of the year-long twentieth anniversary celebrations for ''Holby City''. The episodes are billed as \"dramatic [and] action-packed\".<ref name=\"X\">{{cite press release|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2019/holby-casualty-crossover|title=Holby City and Casualty to air special crossover episodes|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=15 February 2019|accessdate=16 February 2019}}</ref> Both episodes were written by Michelle Lipton and directed by Steve Brett.<ref name=\"X\"/> The episodes see the hospital attacked by a cyber-virus, destroying all electric systems. A predominant story in the episodes follows Connie and ''Holby City'' character [[Jac Naylor]] ([[Rosie Marcel]]) saving the lives of colleagues after two separate major incidents, despite only having one available theatre.<ref name=\"X\"/> Harper described the episode as \"pure, nail-biting, taut, emotional medical drama\".<ref name=\"X\"/> He also praised the production teams of both shows for their logical creation of the episodes, and looked forward to exploring the interactions between the characters from the two shows.<ref name=\"X\"/>\n\nNine ''Casualty'' cast members - Mealing (Connie Beauchamp), Durr (David Hide), Stevenson (Iain Dean), Ryan (Gem Dean), Mohan (Rash Masum), Jafargholi (Marty Kirkby), Griffiths (Elle Gardner), Marshall (Noel Garcia), and Hill (Ruby Spark) - feature in the ''Holby City'' episode of the crossover, originally broadcast on 5 March 2019.<ref name=\"Holby X\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/tv-programme/e/hrf88t/holby-city--s21-e10-powerless/|title=Series 21 \u2013 Episode 10 Powerless|date=21 February 2019|work=[[Radio Times]]|accessdate=21 February 2019}}</ref> The ''Casualty'' episode of the crossover, episode 26 of this series, features the ''Casualty'' cast alongside twelve ''Holby City'' cast members - Marcel (Jac Naylor), [[Bob Barrett (actor)|Bob Barrett]] ([[Sacha Levy]]), [[Hugh Quarshie]] ([[Ric Griffin]]), [[Guy Henry (actor)|Guy Henry]] ([[Henrik Hanssen]]), [[Catherine Russell (actress)|Catherine Russell]] ([[Serena Campbell]]), [[Alex Walkinshaw]] ([[Adrian \"Fletch\" Fletcher]]), [[Kaye Wragg]] ([[Essie Di Lucca]]), [[Jaye Jacobs]] ([[Donna Jackson]]), Marcus Griffiths ([[Xavier Duval|Xavier \"Xav\" Duval]]), Nic Jackman (Cameron Dunn), [[Camilla Arfwedson]] ([[Zosia Self]]), and [[Belinda Owusu]] ([[Nicky McKendrick]]) - and two ''Holby City'' guest actors - Francesca Barrett as Beka Levy and Naomi Katiyo as Darla Johnstone.<ref name=\"33x26\"/>\n\n== Reception ==\nThe drama was nominated in the \"Best Soap (Evening)\" category at the 2018 [[Digital Spy Reader Awards (soap operas)|''Digital Spy'' Reader Awards]]; it came in last place with 3.8% of the total votes.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Robinson |first1=Abby |title=Emmerdale wins big at the Digital Spy Reader Awards 2018 |url=https://www.digitalspy.com/soaps/a25612459/emmerdale-reader-awards-soap-winners-2018/ |accessdate=31 December 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=28 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Episodes ==\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:Episode table|main |background=#80FF8A|overall=5 |series=5|title=25|titleR=<!--To add an episode reference, please refer to Radio Times, then the BBC Media Centre!-->|director=13 |writer=18 |airdate=12 |viewers=9|viewersR=<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/four-screen-dashboard/|title=Four-screen dashboard|publisher=[[Broadcasters' Audience Research Board]]|language=en-GB|access-date=29 July 2019}}</ref>|country=UK|titleT=Episode|episodes=\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1094\n| EpisodeNumber2=1\n| RTitle=[[Episode 1094|Episode 1]]<ref name=\"33x01\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 1|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0bg742d|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writer: Simon Norman; Director: Steve Brett; Producer: Carol Harding|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=11 August 2018}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Simon Norman\n| DirectedBy= Steve Brett\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|08|11|df=y}}\n| Viewers= 5.83\n| ShortSummary= Iain and Ruby visit Mia, a frequent caller claiming to have overdosed. Iain learns Mia has not taken anything, so leaves with Ruby. The pair are sent to Alicia's house, where they find she has a serious arm injury from being pushed through a window by Eddie. On their way to the hospital, Mia jumps from a bridge causing Iain to swerve and crash. A tanker carrying [[butane]] avoids hitting the ambulance, but causes a pile-up on the dual carriageway. Ruby and Alicia are trapped in the ambulance, where Ruby resets Alicia's dislocated elbow. Iain helps treat patients at the scene, while Ruby is sent to the hospital with Mia after being freed from the ambulance. Sam, Jan and Dylan help treat the injured. The tanker explodes just as they get the last remaining casualty out of her car; the force of the explosion causes Sam to slam into the ambulance window. Mia dies and Iain blames himself. At the ambulance station, Sam realises her liver has been nicked by shrapnel and she tries to treat herself. Iain finds Sam and she loses consciousness. He attempts CPR, but Sam dies.\n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1095\n| EpisodeNumber2=2\n| RTitle=Episode 2<ref name=\"33x02\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 2|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0bgznjg|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writer: Patrick Homes; Director: Steve Brett; Producer: Carol Harding|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=18 August 2018}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Patrick Homes\n| DirectedBy= Steve Brett\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|08|18|df=y}}\n| Viewers= 5.30\n| ShortSummary= Iain tells Jan that he had the potential to save Mia's life, ultimately preventing the crash and Sam's death. Jan questions Iain over why there was no record of his and Ruby's attendance to Mia's house, before telling him to alter his statement in order to save his career. Iain is wracked with guilt and decides he cannot lie. He hands his statement in, and is suspended by Jan. Dylan is surprised by the return of Ciara, the woman he met at his alcoholics anonymous meeting. Ciara's alcoholic friend is admitted to the [[emergency department|ED]] after going [[cold turkey]], resulting in a dangerous shock to her body system. Dylan learns that Ciara is also struggling with her own alcoholism. Connie raises her concerns with the senior staff of the hospital that targets are not being met.\n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1096\n| EpisodeNumber2=3\n| RTitle=Episode 3<ref name=\"33x03\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 3|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0bhnkbh|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writers: Marissa Lestrade & Steve Bailie; Director: Thomas Hescott; Producer: Dafydd Llewelyn|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=25 August 2018}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Marissa Lestrade & Steve Bailie\n| DirectedBy= Thomas Hescott\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|08|25|df=y}}\n| Viewers= 5.37\n| ShortSummary= Alicia returns to work earlier than planned and treats a family of five who have been involved in a car crash. She connects with the children in the family as she treats their mother and sister, who is in need of a transplant. Alicia decides she wants to specialise in paediatrics, and informs Connie of her decision. She also goes to courtroom to hear how Eddie pleads to his rape charge; Eddie pleads guilty and Alicia is relieved. Dylan is tasked with clearing out Sam's locker. He brings Jacob along with him and they clean her locker out together. Following his shift, Dylan visits Ciara at her house; the pair share a kiss and Dylan is invited inside. Rash's parents have gone on holiday, giving him the opportunity to invite Gem round for the night. Their evening together is quickly halted however, when his parents abruptly return home after getting the dates wrong on the booking website.\n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1097\n| EpisodeNumber2=4\n| RTitle=Episode 4<ref name=\"33x04\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 4|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0bj85ky|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writer: [[Jeff Povey]]; Director: Thomas Hescott; Producer: Dafydd Llewelyn|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=1 September 2018}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= [[Jeff Povey]]\n| DirectedBy= Thomas Hescott\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|09|01|df=y}}\n| Viewers=5.23\n| ShortSummary= Iain makes a speech at Sam's funeral, but Dylan interrupts and publicly blames Iain for Sam's death. Iain decides he has had enough of Holby, and vows to miss his tribunal hearing and leave for good. When Iain sees Dylan at the hospital, he confronts Dylan and punches him. Jan calms Iain down and helps him see sense, while Dylan later tells Iain he is a good paramedic, encouraging him to attend his hearing. Iain's job is saved, but he continues to hold a grudge against Ruby. Alicia and Ethan treat a young boy and his mother injured by a motorbike. They find unusual bruising on the young boy and work together to uncover what is going on. Jacob and Blake bond as they share fond memories of Sam.\n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1098\n| EpisodeNumber2=5\n| RTitle=Episode 5<ref name=\"33x05\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 5|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0bl27zp|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writers: Jerome Bucchan-Nelson & Dana Fainaru; Director: Judith Dine; Producer: Rebecca Hedderley|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=15 September 2018}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Jerome Bucchan-Nelson & Dana Fainaru\n| DirectedBy= Judith Dine\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|09|15|df=y}}\n| Viewers=5.12\n| ShortSummary= Dylan grows concerned for Ciara when she fails to answer any of his calls and goes missing. Ciara later turns up at the ED after getting drunk, and is found in a cubicle by David, who hides her from Dylan. Dylan soon finds Ciara and learns what David has been up to; he berates David for his actions. Dylan later goes to visit Ciara back at her house, but receives a shock when Ciara's husband opens the door and introduces himself. Iain returns to work following his tribunal hearing, and decides to work alone to get away from Ruby. He finds a homeless Base in a carpark, who has gotten himself into trouble with drug dealers in the aftermath of Mia's death in [[Episode 1093]]. Iain takes Base back to his house and vows to help him get his life back on track. Ethan visits Alicia at her house and repaints her bedroom to help her overcome her recent rape ordeal.\n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1099\n| EpisodeNumber2=6\n| RTitle=Episode 6<ref name=\"33x06\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 6|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0blqskr|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writer: Chris Murray; Director: Judith Dine; Producer: Rebecca Hedderley|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=22 September 2018}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Chris Murray\n| DirectedBy= Judith Dine\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|09|22|df=y}}\n| Viewers=6.00\n| ShortSummary= Dylan tries to avoid Ciara when she arrives at the ED with her husband Joel complaining of abdominal pains, but he later decides to investigate. Dylan learns that Ciara is pregnant, that he is father, and that she is suffering an [[ectopic pregnancy]]. Dylan supports Ciara, but she rejects him, so he heads over to the pub and gets drunk. Blake is inspired to look for his grandmother after hearing an anecdote from Jacob about her. He finds Omo running a local church shop, and introduces himself. Elle warns Blake to be careful around Jacob, as she believes Jacob's relationship with Omo is strained. Iain secures Base a place on the rehabilitation course, but as the pair head to the rehabilitation centre in the ambulance, Iain leaves Base alone to get him something from the shop. When Iain returns to the ambulance, Base has run away, and taken a bag of drugs with him.\n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1100\n| EpisodeNumber2=7\n| RTitle=Episode 7<ref name=\"33x07\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 7|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0bmf87b|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writer: [[Jon Sen]]; Director: Alex Jacob; Producer: Carol Harding|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=29 September 2018}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= [[Jon Sen]]\n| DirectedBy= Alex Jacob\n| OriginalAirDate={{S