motherapy, and that she has up to a couple of months to live. Jacob has Omo's medication tested at the pharmacy, and it is revealed that Jet has been selling her morphine and swapping it. Archie visits Connie in her office, and after she leaves, Connie closes the blinds and takes diazepam. \n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1133\n| EpisodeNumber2=40\n| RTitle=Episode 40<ref name=\"33x40\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 40|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m00069hx|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writer: Claire Miller; Director: Nimer Rashed; Producer: Sean Gleeson|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=22 June 2019}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Claire Miller\n| DirectedBy= Nimer Rashed\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|6|22|df=y}}\n| Viewers=4.33\n| ShortSummary= On her way to work, Duffy assesses the condition of a girl hit by a bus. David assesses Marty and Jade on their ability of taking care of adults with minor illnesses. Jacob discovers blood in Omo's bag, and insists on taking her into hospital. Dylan informs her that her pancreatic tumour is pushing against the wall of her stomach; she refuses treatment but Jacob later convinces her otherwise. Charlie informs the department that although Duffy is not leaving, she will no longer be doing any clinical tasks.  \n| LineColor=80FF8A\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|Casualty (series 33)\n| EpisodeNumber=1134\n| EpisodeNumber2=41\n| RTitle=Episode 41<ref name=\"33x41\">{{cite episode|title=Episode 41|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m0006hk1|series=Casualty|serieslink=Casualty (TV series)|credits=Writer: Rachel Paterson; Director: Julie Edwards; Producer: Kirsty Lane|network=[[BBC]]|station=[[BBC One]]|airdate=29 June 2019}}</ref>\n| WrittenBy= Rachel Paterson\n| DirectedBy= Julie Edwards\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|6|29|df=y}}\n| Viewers=3.99\n| ShortSummary= Jade catches Jacob unsuccessfully trying to find details